Description: Body sherd of Clazomenian black-figured pottery slim neck amphora with handle zone on left; exterior: black-figure decoration (fired partly red) consisting of upper body and tresses of female walking right; at right edge of sherd, tresses of a second female to right.
Curator's comments: For parallels regarding the female figure, see Reading 14.9.76.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GH.014) (Phase 1)
